1. Reading a sf object

#Example
data("Peru")
peru.region <- Peru %>%
  dplyr::group_by(dep) %>%
  summarise()
glimpse(peru.region)
## Rows: 25
## Columns: 2
## $ dep      <chr> "AMAZONAS", "ANCASH", "APURIMAC", "AREQUIPA", "AYACUCHO", "CA…
## $ geometry <GEOMETRY [°]> POLYGON ((-77.77036 -5.7881..., POLYGON ((-77.32594 …
mapview(peru.region,legend = NULL)

2. Transformation of sf object to a feature collection

peru.ee <- peru.region %>%
  pol_as_ee(
    id = c("dep"),
    simplify = 100
  )
